#: src/guides/injection.md:1
msgid "Adding Injection Queries"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:3
msgid ""
"Writing language injection queries allows one to highlight a specific node "
"as a different language. In addition to the [standard](https://tree-sitter."
"github.io/tree-sitter/3-syntax-highlighting.html#language-injection) "
"language injection options used by tree-sitter, there are a few Helix "
"specific extensions that allow for more control."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:7
msgid ""
"An example of a simple query that would highlight all strings as bash in Nix:"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:10
msgid "\"bash\""
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:12
msgid ""
"Another example is this query, which highlights links in comments and "
"keywords like \"TODO\", by reusing the dedicated \"comment\" language:"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:13
msgid ""
"```\n"
"((comment) @injection.content\n"
"  (#set! injection.language \"comment\"))\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:18
msgid "Capture Types"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:20
msgid ""
"`@injection.language` (standard): The captured node may contain the language "
"name used to highlight the node captured by `@injection.content`."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:24
msgid ""
"`@injection.content` (standard): Marks the content to be highlighted as the "
"language captured with `@injection.language` _et al_."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:27
msgid ""
"`@injection.filename` (extension): The captured node may contain a filename "
"with a file-extension known to Helix, highlighting `@injection.content` as "
"that language. This uses the language extensions defined in both the default "
"languages.toml distributed with Helix, as well as user defined languages."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:32
msgid ""
"`@injection.shebang` (extension): The captured node may contain a shebang "
"used to choose a language to highlight as. This also uses the shebangs "
"defined in the default and user `languages.toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:36
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:38
msgid ""
"`injection.combined` (standard): Indicates that all the matching nodes in "
"the tree should have their content parsed as one nested document."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:42
msgid ""
"`injection.language` (standard): Forces the captured content to be "
"highlighted as the given language"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:45
msgid ""
"`injection.include-children` (standard): Indicates that the content node’s "
"entire text should be re-parsed, including the text of its child nodes. By "
"default, child nodes’ text will be excluded from the injected document."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:49
msgid ""
"`injection.include-unnamed-children` (extension): Same as `injection.include-"
"children` but only for unnamed child nodes."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:52
msgid "Predicates"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:54
msgid ""
"`#eq?` (standard): The first argument (a capture) must be equal to the "
"second argument (a capture or a string)."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:58
msgid ""
"`#match?` (standard): The first argument (a capture) must match the regex "
"given in the second argument (a string)."
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/injection.md:62
msgid ""
"`#any-of?` (standard): The first argument (a capture) must be one of the "
"other arguments (strings)."
msgstr ""
